  <title>get_actor_at_pos</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(Clutter.PickMode, gint, gint)
@returns(Clutter.Actor)
def get_actor_at_pos(pick_mode, x, y)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Checks the scene at the coordinates @x and @y and returns a pointer
to the <link xref="Clutter.Actor">Clutter.Actor</link> at those coordinates.</p><p>By using @pick_mode it is possible to control which actors will be
painted and thus available.</p><p>if any</p>

